</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uraiyaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaiyaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 545<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/7/02 8:57:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3331.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Warriors</span><hr size=1> I think everyone should post the &quot;wtb upgrades for class_01&quot; on druids board.  Reason being, druids whine so much so verant might overlook and give you the upgrade you want.  Anyway, back to the topic.<br>
<br>
I love warriors, especially the ones that can taunt.  Even though most of them always tell me that they never train the skill.  But I still love them.  Warriors' dmg maybe not be as good as rogues, but the taunting, tanking is really amazing.  What makes a good warrior imo is the ability to oversee the whole situation.  Not just taunting, tanking one mob blindly.  The good warriors will always switch target when needed, i.e. if a mob is unmezable and it's beating on the clerics/chanters, he/she will switch target immediately and tried to get as many targets on him/her as possible (ae taunt or just switch targets back and force to make sure they all stay on him).  The one warrior that I group the most with is Ayiar (duh), he's really good on this part due to the many lvl's training of Raiya doing /y.  I haven't have chances to group with many other warriors, but the few chances I had, Minimannen will have to be another one that I can trust in a messy situation.  This does not mean they are the only 2 good warriors, I am sure there are many other fine warriors out there, I just haven't have the chance to group enough to see the ability someone else's have.<br>
<br>
I used to think warrior gotta be the most easy class to play.  But after I've seen what a good warrior has to do, I have to say, no, it's not easy at all.  They have to press more than just 1212121212 + auto attack.<br>
<br>
WTB more warriors who are more than just a meat shield <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90395>Raiya</a> / <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90580>Jinling</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucorpsedagain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CorpsedAgain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 900<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/7/02 10:40:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3331.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 2)Increase in taunt effectiveness (mid-Velious ?)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Ummm, taunt is essentially worthless.  The only thing that gets agro is if everyone gives warriors a headstart on a mob or by procs.  Let me assure you, if there is a warrior in your group who is not holding agro, it is not because they are not hitting taunt.  It is because taunt is broken.  But, I'm not gonna moan and whine and threaten to delete my account (ahem).  I'll continue to play and verant will eventually fix it. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198911>Corpsed</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubigemnoseandhow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bigemnose andhow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/7/02 11:41:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3331.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warriors</span><hr size=1> For the person that said that warriors do a great job at their intended tasks, I don't think you are right.<br>
<br>
The very question of how would you make up a party with today's classes came up on my guild's message board just this week.  After much discussion, the list came down to:  Cleric, Enchanter, Shaman, Rogue, Mage, and Shadowknight.<br>
<br>
Notice the lack of warrior in that list.  The number one reason and practically unanimously agreed upon reason was that the Shadowknight can out taunt the warrior by a long shot, and the cleric can keep the shadowknight alive just as good as he/she could keep a warrior alive.<br>
<br>
Like it or not, the warrior just isn't the number one pick for most groups these days because the Shadowknight can out taunt the warrior by a long shot and has just slightly less hit points.  Why Verant doesn't just admit that they screwed up by creating both the shadowknight/paladin and the warrior is beyond me.  They should simply eliminate the warrior class and just migrate the few things that the warrior does that the shadowknight/paladin doesnt do to the shadowknight/paladin.  At such time, they should give warriors the ability to choose to become a paladin or a shadowknight upon the next time they logon after the patch, and that would be the end of the age old discussion of how sucky the warrior has become.<br>
<br>
Admit it Verant... the warrior is a dead race.<br>
<br>
Sorry... stepping down from my soap box and putting my Save Against Flames +50 rings on.<br>
